# TCP/IP Model – Hands-on Learning

This section is a practical breakdown of the TCP/IP model with real packet analysis, labs, and protocol-level understanding using Wireshark and networking tools.

The focus is not theory memorization — but understanding how data actually moves across networks.

---

# What I Practiced

## Core Model Understanding
- TCP/IP layers breakdown
- OSI vs TCP/IP mapping
- Encapsulation & decapsulation flow

## Protocol Behavior
- TCP vs UDP behavior differences
- DNS resolution process
- HTTP vs HTTPS communication flow

## Packet-Level Analysis
- TCP 3-way handshake (SYN, SYN-ACK, ACK)
- DNS query tracing in Wireshark
- HTTPS TLS handshake observation

## Real Network Flow Thinking
- How browser connects to server
- How packets travel through layers
- Where routing + NAT happens

